              ----ccoonnffiigguurree ----ppeennddiinngg.

       ----ttrriiggggeerrss
              Cancels a previous ----nnoo--ttrriiggggeerrss (since dpkg 1.14.17).

EEXXIITT SSTTAATTUUSS
       00      The requested action was  successfully  performed.   Or  a  check  or  assertion
              command returned true.

       11      A check or assertion command returned false.

       22      Fatal  or unrecoverable error due to invalid command-line usage, or interactions
              with the system, such as accesses to the database, memory allocations, etc.

EENNVVIIRROONNMMEENNTT
   EExxtteerrnnaall eennvviirroonnmmeenntt
       PPAATTHH   This variable is expected to be defined in the  environment  and  point  to  the
              system paths where several required programs are to be found. If it's not set or
              the programs are not found, ddppkkgg will abort.

       HHOOMMEE   If set, ddppkkgg will use it as the directory from which to read the  user  specific
              configuration file.

       TTMMPPDDIIRR If set, ddppkkgg will use it as the directory in which to create temporary files and
              directories.

       SSHHEELLLL  The program ddppkkgg will execute when starting a new  interactive  shell,  or  when
              spawning a command via a shell.

       PPAAGGEERR
       DDPPKKGG__PPAAGGEERR
              The  program ddppkkgg will execute when running a pager, for example when displaying
              the conffile differences.  If SSHHEELLLL is not set, «sshh» will be used instead.   The
              DDPPKKGG__PPAAGGEERR overrides the PPAAGGEERR environment variable (since dpkg 1.19.2).

       DDPPKKGG__CCOOLLOORRSS
              Sets  the  color  mode  (since dpkg 1.18.5).  The currently accepted values are:
              aauuttoo (default), aallwwaayyss and nneevveerr.

       DDPPKKGG__FFOORRCCEE
              Sets the force flags (since dpkg 1.19.5).  When this  variable  is  present,  no
              built-in  force defaults will be applied.  If the variable is present but empty,
              all force flags will be disabled.

       DDPPKKGG__FFRROONNTTEENNDD__LLOOCCKKEEDD
              Set by a package manager frontend to notify dpkg that it should not acquire  the
              frontend lock (since dpkg 1.19.1).

